Locals have called on the Government to urgently erect guardrails on the bridge across River Rupingazi.
 This follows an accident in which a prison warder died on Monday. 
 ALSO READ:

Three bodies of accident victims yet to be identified 

 They said the accident would not have been fatal had there been guardrails to stop the car from plunging into the river.
 The driver lost control, veered off the bridge and plunged into the river. Attempts by passers-by to rescue him were in vain.




(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});

  Kirimari MCA Morris Muchiri said many people had died at the bridge and called on Kenya National Highways Authority to erect guardrails to prevent more deaths.
  
